WEBVTT

00:00:01.199 --> 00:00:08.279
There is no doubt that we are living in critical times hard to deal with, just as the Apostle

00:00:08.279 --> 00:00:15.320
Paul prophesied under inspiration in 2 Timothy chapter 3.

00:00:15.320 --> 00:00:25.440
Many times we have read Matthew chapter 24, Mark 13, Luke 21, and Revelation chapter 6.

00:00:25.440 --> 00:00:35.079
But who would ever have known how deeply a pandemic, so-called natural disasters, violence,

00:00:35.079 --> 00:00:43.159
and unrest would affect us economically, physically, and even emotionally?

00:00:43.159 --> 00:00:48.159
Some of you dear friends face unimaginable hardships.

00:00:48.159 --> 00:00:55.920
Many have experienced loss of loved ones, imprisonment, physical abuse, sickness, financial

00:00:55.920 --> 00:01:04.439
problems, and sometimes a number of these or other circumstances all at the same time.

00:01:04.439 --> 00:01:09.640
You dear brothers and sisters are in our prayers.

00:01:09.640 --> 00:01:19.599
With this in mind, the theme for our program is, in difficult times, Jehovah always comforts.

00:01:19.599 --> 00:01:26.359
A scripture that's become familiar to Jehovah's people is 2 Corinthians chapter 1, verses

00:01:26.359 --> 00:01:28.959
3 and 4.

00:01:28.959 --> 00:01:36.480
Praise be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father of tender mercies,

00:01:36.480 --> 00:01:43.319
and the God of all comfort, who comforts us in all our trials, so that we may be able

00:01:43.319 --> 00:01:50.879
to comfort others in any sort of trial, with the comfort that we receive from God.

00:01:50.879 --> 00:01:59.040
The study Bible says this regarding the expression the Father of tender mercies.

00:01:59.040 --> 00:02:05.400
The Greek noun rendered tender mercies is here used to describe a feeling of compassion

00:02:05.400 --> 00:02:08.199
or pity for others.

00:02:08.199 --> 00:02:14.240
God is called the Father, or the source of tender mercies because compassion emanates

00:02:14.240 --> 00:02:18.479
from Him and is part of His nature.

00:02:18.479 --> 00:02:25.080
Such tender feelings move Him to act mercifully in behalf of His faithful servants who are

00:02:25.080 --> 00:02:29.030
suffering tribulation.

00:02:29.030 --> 00:02:34.469
Regarding the phrase, the God of all comfort, it continues.

00:02:34.469 --> 00:02:39.949
The Greek noun here rendered comfort literally means, a calling to one's side.

00:02:39.949 --> 00:02:45.949
It conveys the idea of standing next to a person, helping or encouraging him when he's undergoing

00:02:45.949 --> 00:02:49.030
trials or feeling sad.

00:02:49.030 --> 00:02:56.270
God uses His powerful active force to give comfort and help, in situations that from a human

00:02:56.270 --> 00:03:00.590
viewpoint seem hopeless.

00:03:00.590 --> 00:03:03.189
Think about what that means.

00:03:03.189 --> 00:03:10.629
And Jehovah wants us to know that whatever we face, he is by our side helping us when

00:03:10.629 --> 00:03:13.229
we're undergoing any sort of trial.

00:03:13.229 --> 00:03:16.949
No, he did not promise that he'd remove our trials.

00:03:16.949 --> 00:03:24.509
Rather, he eases our misery or grief whenever we undergo difficulties.

00:03:24.509 --> 00:03:32.509
What a beautiful word picture of God standing next to us, especially when things seem hopeless.

00:03:33.349 --> 00:03:37.110
We invite you to do a personal study project.

00:03:37.110 --> 00:03:43.430
Using the publication Research Guide for Jehovah's Witnesses or the Watchtower Online Library,

00:03:43.430 --> 00:03:47.389
do a word search on comfort.

00:03:47.389 --> 00:03:55.110
You'll be drawn even closer to Jehovah and appreciate His unmatched desire and ability

00:03:55.110 --> 00:03:58.639
to comfort.

00:03:58.639 --> 00:04:06.479
Jehovah also inspired Paul to show how he would stand by us to comfort us.

00:04:06.479 --> 00:04:12.080
Notice Romans chapter 15 and verse 4.

00:04:12.080 --> 00:04:19.319
For all the things that were written beforehand were written for our instruction so that through

00:04:19.319 --> 00:04:27.720
our endurance and through the comfort from the Scriptures, we might have hope.

00:04:27.879 --> 00:04:35.959
Time limits us from going into all the ways that the Bible does this.

00:04:35.959 --> 00:04:38.879
But let's take some examples.

00:04:38.879 --> 00:04:45.680
A scripture that Jehovah's people have often meditated on in recent times is found in Jeremiah

00:04:45.680 --> 00:04:54.709
chapter 29, when Jehovah inspired Jeremiah to convey his message to the Jews.

00:04:54.750 --> 00:05:00.310
