00:05:08.389 --> 00:05:13.629
Notice His words in Jeremiah chapter 29, verse 10.

00:05:13.629 --> 00:05:20.910
When 70 years at Babylon are fulfilled, I will turn my attention to you.

00:05:20.910 --> 00:05:27.550
God told these Jewish exiles that they would remain in captivity for a long time.

00:05:27.550 --> 00:05:32.949
Then He made clear to them that He had a peaceful future in mind.

00:05:32.949 --> 00:05:39.269
The latter part of that verse says, and I will make good by promise by bringing you back

00:05:39.269 --> 00:05:41.230
to this place.

00:05:41.230 --> 00:05:46.670
In verse 11, He says, I will know the thoughts that I am thinking toward you, declares

00:05:47.629 --> 00:05:55.790
of peace and not of calamity, to give you a future and a hope.

00:05:55.790 --> 00:06:00.149
God did make good on His promise to those Israelites.

00:06:00.149 --> 00:06:04.509
He let them know that their future was to be a bright one.

00:06:04.509 --> 00:06:12.470
Regarding Jeremiah 29, 11, one commentary states,

00:06:12.470 --> 00:06:18.709
it is difficult to find a more wonderful promise anywhere in Scripture that expresses

00:06:18.709 --> 00:06:26.949
the tender compassion of Yahweh, Jehovah, toward these exiles and setting before them at last

00:06:26.949 --> 00:06:32.550
a real reason for optimism and expectation.

00:06:32.550 --> 00:06:39.790
Jehovah's promise strengthened men such as Jeremiah, Ezekiel, and Daniel.

00:06:39.790 --> 00:06:47.470
Jehovah reassured the Jews by repeating His promise at Jeremiah 31, verse 17,

00:06:47.470 --> 00:06:50.910
and there is a hope for your future.

00:06:50.910 --> 00:06:55.949
Your sons will return to their own territory.

00:06:55.949 --> 00:07:03.949
Sure enough, just as Jehovah foretold, Babylon was conquered by the Persian king Cyrus,

00:07:03.949 --> 00:07:08.149
who allowed the exiles Jews to return to their homeland.

00:07:08.149 --> 00:07:13.670
After 70 years of captivity, they were back in Jerusalem.

00:07:13.670 --> 00:07:18.870
Jehovah made good on His promise.

00:07:18.870 --> 00:07:22.550
What does that have to do with us today?

00:07:22.550 --> 00:07:30.470
The fulfilled promises of Jehovah assure us that His promises to us will come true

00:07:30.470 --> 00:07:37.589
in spite of surrounding circumstances as He said, I will make good my promise.

00:07:37.589 --> 00:07:43.910
How comforting to know that, but we know that the greatest expression of Jehovah's comfort

00:07:44.709 --> 00:07:48.149
is His only begotten Son, Jesus.

00:07:49.670 --> 00:07:56.310
During His time on earth He gave people hope, Jesus engaged in a marvelous ministry

00:07:56.310 --> 00:08:00.629
healing the sick, performing powerful works, and most important,

00:08:01.269 --> 00:08:03.430
teaching people about God's kingdom.

00:08:04.310 --> 00:08:12.310
